    "b = s.bacon()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "13. What can you do to save a programme from crashing if it encounters an error?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Yes, we can use exception handling to protect it from crashing depending upon the type of error we can use except clause."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "14. What is the purpose of the try clause? What is the purpose of the except clause?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The try block is used to check code for errors i.e the code inside the try block will execute when there is no error in the program.\n",
    "\n",
    "Whereas the code inside the except block will execute whenever the program encounters some error in the previous try block."
   ]
  }
